#!/usr/bin/python3

def look_and_say(n):
    term = "1"
    for _ in range(1, n):
        next_term = ""
        i = 0
        while i < len(term):
            count = 1
            while i + 1 < len(term) and term[i] == term[i + 1]:
                i += 1
                count += 1
            next_term += str(count) + term[i]
            i += 1
        term = next_term
    return term

a30 = look_and_say(31)
print("a[30]:", a30)
print("len(a[30]):", len(a30))
